  "body": "From [current kubedns codes](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/dns/dns.go#L153-L162). The `kubedns` starts with running services and endpoints store controller, and setups the ready signal once `Get(kubernetesSvcName)` returns.\n\nAlthough store controllers will start with `list`ing all objects and sync, there is no guarantee that all existing services/endpoints can get fully updated into treecache at the point `Get(kubernetesSvcName)` returns. Especially when scaling out `kubedns` for a huge cluster that has lots of services/endpoints. Ramping up the new `kubedns` may take a while, and those unready dns servers may got exposed ahead because `Get(kubernetesSvcName)` returns quickly.\n\n@bowei @bprashanth @thockin \n",
